x4freetext: U120M isochronous cyclotron
Self-supporting Li (cooled by 5 deg-C alcohol
stream) with a carbon beam stopper was irradiated at
59Co disks (99.9% purity, 15 mm in diam, 0.25 mm in
thickness).
Stacks of foils (Au, Co, Nb) were placed at two
distances (48 mm and 88 mm) from the neutron
production target
Two HPGe detectors used: 23% and 50% efficiency,
FWHM 1.8 keV at 1.3 MeV (60Co gamma-line)
Irradiated for ~46000 sec to ~82000 sec at each
proton energy (average current of ~4.21 to 4.84 uA)
Unfolded in the VITAMIN-J+ bin energy structure
assuming the 7Li(p,n) neutron spectra evaluated by
MCNPX with LA-150h cross section data libraries.
The cross section in the EAF 2007 library was assumed
for the cross section lower than the quasi-
monoenergetic peak of the lowest energy run (~16 MeV)
Uncertainty propagated from
Activity determination    (1-2%)
Detector efficiency         (2%)
Beam charge                 (5%)
Neutron flux determination (10%)
Data received from the author
Preliminary data (Eva Simeckova, 2015-06-23)
Approved by Eva Simeckova (2015-06-24)
